        "title": "feat(durable): add workflow kernel primitives",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR adds the native durable workflow kernel primitives.\n\nIt introduces:\n\n- durable workflow run, step, event, ref, link, timer, and signal types;\n- SQLite local-first store;\n- run and step claims;\n- timer and signal recovery primitives;\n- fan-in helper;\n- in-process workflow registry;\n- one-shot durable executor for registered safe step handlers.\n\n## Why\n\nThis creates the minimal native kernel needed before OpenClaw can make long-running agent work restart-visible, retryable, and resumable.\n\n## Stack Note\n\nThis is PR 2 in the durable core stack and should be reviewed after PR 1.\n\nGitHub may show cumulative diff until PR 1 is merged because the branch is pushed from a fork and the upstream repository does not allow branch bases for this stack.\n\nIncremental branch:\n\n- `mjnkao:codex/openclaw-x-durable-pr2-core-kernel`\n\n## Validation\n\n- `npm test -- --run src/durable src/gateway/server-methods/durable.test.ts extensions/workboard/src/gateway.test.ts extensions/workboard/src/store.test.ts`\n- `npm run tsgo:core`\n- `npm run build`\n",
